b'' b'which version of the bible do you consider to be the most' b'accurate translation?' b'' b"well, knowing greek and hebrew, i'm probably not as picky about translations" b'as i would be if english translations were my only source of information.' b'but...' b'' b'(1) any verse that comes out substantially different in different trans-' b'lations is almost certainly unclear in the original.' b'' b'(2) it is very bad practice to "shop" for a translation that fits your own' b'doctrinal positions.' b'' b'personally, i still like the rsv. nrsv and nasv are also very good.' b'' b'i have a strong preference for editions that do _not_ indent the beginning' b'of each verse as if verses were paragraphs. the verse numbering is a' b'relatively modern addition and should not be given undue prominence.' b'' b'--' b':- michael a. covington, associate research scientist b':- the university of georgia phone b':- athens, georgia u.s.a. amateur radio n4tmi 